<Text>Working with Jorge Arce was a pleasure!

I visited the store with my dad and sister just to browse. Jorge greeted us and prompted the conversation on what experience / pain points I was having with my current mattress. I didn‚Äôt plan to commit to anything that day - but Jorge definitely went above and beyond to help me feel satisfied and comfortable with my purchase!

He stuck to my budget and didn‚Äôt oversell me on anything which I appreciated. He was patient and respectful of our experience in testing out the different mattresses. Jorge answered all of my questions with ease, referring back to the manual to confirm minor details - a strong contrast with my visit to Jerome‚Äôs just the day before. He offered us a great deal on the power base and discounts on accessories such as the black ice pillows and protective cover. I ordered the Beauty Rest Pressure Smart Medium/Plush paired with the Mattress Firm 900 Adjustable Base. Note that the mattress is more on the firm side (will have to update this review once I‚Äôve had the bed for a couple months to comment further); the lumbar customization on the base was also a huge plus over the tier below it. We scheduled the delivery to arrive just two days later and I left the store feeling very excited for my new bed!

I had follow up questions after my visit and Jorge picked up the phone and answered them immediately. The delivery time frame was between 10:15-12:15 and the movers arrived before 11am. The set-up was quick and I had no issues with operating the power base. This was one of the best customer service experiences I‚Äôve had. My mom loves my new bed and now wants to purchase the same set-up, so we‚Äôll be seeing Jorge again very soon. If you need a new mattress, go see him! You will not be disappointed :)

<pics>None</pics>< text>
There's a good selection of about a dozen or so different flavors that are changed out periodically with other flavors. You're given a little bowl and gloves to serve yourself; you can choose as many different flavors as you can fit in your cup too. Then choose and scoop yourself some toppings - choose from things like candies, cookies, fresh fruit and/or sprinkles. Once you're done, you place your order on a scale and the weight determines your total price. Today when I can in it was unusually hot outside, so I was very thankful for the cold water that was also available for customers!< /text>

< Name>
Grant ‚ÄúAlexander‚Äù Hammel-Davis</Name>
< Review>
This is a very convenient option for those visiting the Avenue of the Arts Hotel, a real hidden gem. Very convenient with their parking validation as well. Make sure to check out their nice happy hour specials, a great way to relax after work. Both the main restaurant area and their lounge are perfect places to unwind. Our server Alex was phenomenal, she was on point from start to finish in every way. She gave me some samples of Eberle red wine and was over-achieving in every way imaginable. Her entire demeanor was that of someone who was dedicated to ensuring we were having an amazing time, and obviously the quality of the food, et cetera, is important, but having someone display such professionalism and friendliness takes the meal to an entirely different level. Her positive and warm vibe along with her perfect recommendations on what to order made the visit several times better, literally. The location here is great and there's a really good selection of cocktails too. We were in the area to enjoy Handel's Messiah at the Segerstrom Center for the Arts, which is another fantastic place to visit, so it was very convenient for everybody. For such a high-end location and set of offerings, all the prices and items are presented with significant value. There are also many things to do in the surrounding area around South Coast Plaza. My food was very tasty and well prepared, the cooks are experts here. Too many good things to discuss here, but you definitely don't want to miss out. The design is beautiful with the pond and landscape, it really has such a delightful and pleasant touch. I highly recommend others stop by here, no need to worry about COVID since they've got every single safety precaution in place, I have no complaints whatsoever.</Review>

<Review>I will give it another try again in the next day or two. Will be here over the next week or so.. Tonight's dinner for two with tip over $170.00  Food over salted, wine pairing above average. My spouse's Salmon was over salted, but she still liked it. I was very surprised when I asked if this was wild or farm raised fish, and was told farm raised. hmmmm. I will rate again after a few more meals. Again the wine pairing from Appetizers going into our Entrees and ending out with our Desserts was 5 stars. <UserId.>103385590214027045303<//UserId.>< name>
Naidona Ott</name>
<Date>1582396996317<//Date><rating>2<//rating>< review>
Although it's a beautiful restaurant and at our visit we recieved excellent service,  we really all just come for the food. And that's where we found them lacking. We came for brunch and our reservation was for 9am. There were two other tables seated when we arrived. My husband ordered the classic with poached eggs. He found it to be just ok but whoever plated,  lazily threw on the poached eggs and they were swimming on the plate along side the potatoes.  This seems to be a theme. I ordered the farro bowl with poached eggs and it was also swimming in egg water. I find that extremely unappetizing and just laziness in the kitchen.  I also ordered the yogurt parfait. I'm assuming that they prepared it hours before service because it was so watery that the yogurt had a curdled consistency.  Again felt like the kitchen not being thoughtful but rather looking for the easy way to prepare. My daughter had the pancakes which were just plain pancakes and what you would expect. Her smoothie we were told was prepared in bulk as well prior to service, so you can imagine the consistency.  Smoothies are quite easy to make...again a kitchen trying to make things easy for themselves at the expense of their diners. We found the silver trumpet very similar to a diner. Unfortunately we were looking for a higher level and quality of food. But, if you love mediocre diners this spot is for you!</review>

<user_name>Bob Woodcock<//user_name>< user>
103432899897739881926< /user>
<gmapID>0x80dcdf271ebf5235:0x263ea49b96a22513<//gmapID>< Time>
1579113733520<//Time>
<Review>We had the charcuterie board for the appetizer, which was delicious, and the best part of the meal.
For the main, I ordered the rack of lamb, which was seasoned with too much salt, and what I believe was cayenne pepper, which wound up overpowering the flavor of the lamb. The others in my party ordered the sea bass, and they also complained about some bizarre flavors on the plate.
For dessert, I ordered the Tiramisu. What came out was a peculiar interpretation of tiramisu. It was more of a coffee/cheesecake (entirely bereft of cream, or lady fingers) with coffee slush on the top. If you've never been served coffee slush at a restaurant before, it is with good reason.
The redeeming qualities that prevent this from being a one star review is that the staff were friendly, the restaurant was clean, the area is lovely, and the appetizer was great.< /Review><pictures>None<//pictures><Resp>None</Resp></record>
</dataset><record>
<Name>Rebecca Clark<//Name><Date>1556732305588< /Date><response>None< /response><pictures>None</pictures>< review>
We've enjoyed the bar in the past but this was our first time dining. We enjoyed Easter brunch (four in party). Brunch was wonderful: good selection of typical breakfast faire such as made to order omelettes, chicken n waffles, hash browns plus salmon, cod, roast beef, lamb, pasta, sliders, and more desserts than you can possibly eat. Wait staff were on point, friendly and attentive as they kept our bottomless mimosas full. What I enjoyed equally was the price. Most brunch spots up their price for major holidays, not Silver Trumpet! The price was very reasonable. Highly recommend enjoying The Silver Trumpet.</review>

<Rate>3< /Rate>< review>
We went at the invitation of the Silver Trumpet to our building which is next door. The invitation included complementary appetizer. We sat an ordered from the happy hour menu which we where told are only $5.00. When they arrived on plate had a finger print from the mustard dressing on it. The rest of the food was nothing to write home about, I forgot to mention that they ran out of chicken wings, really! When another of our guest tried to order a drink they could not make it and the drink he re-ordered came in different type of glass. Back to the complementary appetizer they never came while I was there. They brought one plate of wings which they were suppose to be out of for the 6 of us. When I received my bill they charged full price for everything. Services also left a lot to be desired. Even though it is right next door I will walk across the street to T.G.I.F.</review>

<Text>Read my other reviews.. I tend to write great reviews, but I live next to this place, wanted to like it.. really wanted to like it.... but it was ABSOLUTELY THE WORST MEAL I HAD IN YEARS.

First, drinks.  I ordered directly from their menu.  First I ordered the prosecco and was told they don't have it.  I then ordered another sparkling white from their list, they didn't have that as well.

I ordered a martini from the martini list... they said they couldn't make it.. (3 different drink requests, are you kidding me?)

so I then ordered a pinot noir, FROM THEY'RE LIST AGAIN~!  Didn't have it.

So I then said "red"?   Do you have anything red?? ... finally I got my drink ordered filled.

I ordered the sliders and the wings.  I took one bite of the sliders and nearly choked down the piece of meat into my napkin.  I MEAN SERIOUSLY, when was the last time you had a slider that wasn't edible?????

Leave it to this place... The slider was cooked on something that tasted like the oldest FISH in the entire sea.... GOD FORBID MY SLIDER TASTED THAT ROTTEN FROM FISH... I can only imagine what the fish must of tasted like.

Moving forward, I got the beat salad with blue cheese... PLEASE REALIZE THERE WASN'T ONE ONCE OF BLUE CHEESE ON THE PLATE.

Not one crumble, not one sauce, NOTHING.

Ohh well, the beats by themselves were pretty tasty.

The Wings.. were OK.  I didn't vomit there and there wasn't anything missing from my plate but it was a basic dish... but isn't that true of sliders??

I had dessert.. GOT TO SAY THE DESSERT WAS REALLY GOOD.

I'd go back for dessert if it weren't for the threat of food poisoning.

WON'T EVER GO BACK.. NOT EVEN FOR A DRINK.  They need to CANN EVERYONE WHO WORKS THERE and START FROM SCRATCH, or just burn the place down.  I live within walking's distance from this place but I"ll walk the extra block to eat something edible from SCOTT's instead.

< text>
Good spot near LGB Long Beach Airport. About 10 minutes by bus, 5 by car, to the airport, so it's a convenient place if you're flying out, or meeting someone who's flying in, and you want a place to wait, or get together, before or after the flight. I was there at lunch time, and I think the only food option was hot dogs. But the food and drink prices were good, the service fast and friendly, and they had multiple TV's and quickly switched one so I could watch "my" Boston Bruins.<//text>

And  be thankful for that there are people out there working in any place  or job they have . Working to help themselves & at the same time helping us the public get thru our

2) clerks are always very friendly, and often competent and helpful
3) parking is plentiful, as long as you drive over the curb and park in the dirt lot just to the North

< text>
Just got off the phone with Francine over with the Oceanside office. She was super friendly, professional, kind, and patiently explained some of the SSA process with me. I just want to encourage people out there going through the SSA process to try to be patient, kind, and remember that these employees at SSA all have a heart, and care about people, and are honestly doing their very best within the guidelines, rules and regulations set forth for them to follow via their employer, aka the "US Government/ SSA Administration". If you need help understanding, just ask. If you need an answer repeated, just ask. If you're concerned, just let them know. We're all humans, on this spinning ball, navigating our way through this Pandemic, and it's been literally making public workers, not to mention the public, TIRED. The essential workers are exhausted, and yet they still do their job, no matter the changes, the new processes, or the need to pivot and change direction, sometimes on a dime. Just be kind. Thank You, Francine, and to the other SSA employees there, hats off <3. Enjoy your upcoming holiday, take some deep breaths, we appreciate you!< /text>

< Review>
I went to Jesse's Muffler & Brakes, after a high estimate from another shop. I already had a Flowmaster Flowfx muffler and S.S. tip, and wanted the stock muffler replaced with the two, and was thinking of possibly replacing the stock cat-back tubing on my PT Cruiser.
Jesse's was a great guy. Personable, and professional. He recommended just the muffler and tip change, instead of the whole  exhaust being done after he took a look at it. That's honesty. Got to love it.  Most places would just tell you that you should get the more expensive job done.
Jesse gave me a great price, and his employee had it done super fast.
I will definitely go back to his place if I need any work done, and would highly recommend anyone, to go to his shop if they need any work done on their car or truck, even if it's just a PT Cruiser, lol.
Great work, great price, and great people.
Thanks Jesse.< /Review>

< Review>
Very courteous staff. I usually just change my own oil, but was busy and took it here instead. When I walked in, the customer rep yelled out (something like) "New Customer" and all employees cheered. That was pretty cool.
All these type of "lube shops" always have suggestions beyond the standard oil change but the couple of times I've gone to a lube shop previously, they almost make you feel bad for not buying their recommendations. Not here. The staff was very honest about their suggestions. I decided to follow up with my mechanic just to be safe and he agreed with most of their recommendations.

I was in and out in like 25-30 minutes. They had a nice waiting area for a mechanic-type shop. I'll probably continue to change my oil most of the time, but for that once every couple years that I don't, this Jiffy Lube ddid an awesome job!< /Review>

< Review>
Pros: Excellent service here! They are very quick and to the point while still remaining very thorough. The unit I was assigned was also very convenient. It's also very secure.

Cons: Pricing was too expensive for the small 5x10 unit I was using. $55/month with autopay, and my first month wasn't $1 like their promo and reps said it would be. Also, whenever I'd go back there would be a bunch of dust inside my unit from being blown inside from the outside of it. A lot of that dirt got on my bed and on my other belongings, which are very sensitive items.
*Update: Also, my second time here I got a 5x10 unit again, but this time they gave me a worse unit that is very exposed and requires 2 locks that they charged me twice the price for ($40). Totally not fair. The agent on the phone said I only needed 1 lock, but in person they said otherwise. Now I have 3 locks by them that I paid a total of $60 for. Ridiculous how they make their money.

Overall, I would say this place can be okay if you really need to butcher your move. If anyone decides to come here, just be cautious and make sure all of your items are covered and clean at all times. Don't hesitate to confront them about anything and if you have a problem then let them know.<//Review>

I was told to come down to purchase a new lock and to make sure nothing was stolen, that was not the case. Went to the office couldn't make a police report because, my name is not the primary on the account. When I finally did talk to the police department the girls in the office at StorQuest gave the officer a hard time when trying to get the video surveillance. I have renter's insurance through StorQuest so I have a claim that is in the process of being handled. Even though this is going on 3 months now and im not getting anywhere. I feel like I'm having to jump through hoops all the way around just to get compensated for my lost items.
